org.cloudbus.foggatewaylib.core

Class InMemoryStore<E extends Data,C extends InMemoryStore.BackingCollection>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cloudbus.foggatewaylib.core.Store<E>
      • org.cloudbus.foggatewaylib.core.InMemoryStore<E,C>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of the elements stored.

    public class InMemoryStore<E extends Data,C extends InMemoryStore.BackingCollection>
extends Store<E>
    Implementation of a Store that uses a custom extension of a LinkedList, SortedLinkedList for storing the data in memory.

    Furthermore, for any request id, a SortedLinkedList links all the elements for that request, speeding up time required to query data from the same request.

    The choice to use a sorted linked list is to have O(1) insertion in the tail, since it is the most common application scenario, while keeping the possibility of out-of-order insertion

    Author:
    Riccardo Mancini
    See Also:
    SortedLinkedList
